{"title_page": "Jordan Hugill", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Jordan Hugill\n| image               = Jordan Hugill.jpg\n| caption             = Hugill with Preston North End in 2016\n| fullname            = Jordan Thomas Hugill<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=18 February 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1992|06|04}}\n| birth_place         = [[Middlesbrough]], England\n| height              = {{height|ft=6|in=0}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Player Profile |url=http://mobile.pnefc.net/team/player-profile/jordan-hugill/25 |website=mobile.pnefc.net |accessdate=2 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011081207/http://mobile.pnefc.net/team/player-profile/jordan-hugill/25|archive-date=11 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub         = [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]<br>(on loan from [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]])\n| clubnumber          = 9\n| youthyears1         = 2007\u20132008| youthclubs1 = [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]]\n| years1              = 2008\u20132009| clubs1 = [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]]                 | caps1 =     | goals1 = \n| years2              = 2009\u20132010| clubs2 = [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]]                               | caps2 =     | goals2 = \n| years3              = 2011     | clubs3 = [[Jerez Industrial CF|Jerez Industrial]]                 | caps3 =     | goals3 = \n| years4              = 2011\u20132012| clubs4 = [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]]                         | caps4 =     | goals4 = \n| years5              = 2012     | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]] (loan)            | caps5 =     | goals5 = \n| years6              = 2013\u20132014| clubs6 = [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]                             | caps6 =  20 | goals6 =   4\n| years7              = 2013     | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] (loan)                    | caps7 =   7 | goals7 =   5\n| years8              = 2014\u20132018| clubs8 = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]             | caps8 = 103 | goals8 =  23\n| years9              = 2015     | clubs9 = \u2192 [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] (loan)        | caps9 =   6 | goals9 =   1\n| years10             = 2015     | clubs10= \u2192 [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan)    | caps10=   8 | goals10=   4\n| years11             = 2018\u2013    | clubs11= [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]                 | caps11=   3 | goals11=   0\n| years12             = 2018\u20132019| clubs12= \u2192 [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] (loan)            | caps12=  37 | goals12=   6 \n| years13             = 2019\u2013    | clubs13= \u2192 [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] (loan)| caps13=   35| goals13=   11\n| club-update         = 18:00, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Jordan Thomas Hugill''' (born 4 June 1992) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]], on loan from [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].\n\nA relative late comer to the professional game, he had spells with non-league sides [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]], [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]], [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]] and [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]], and also spent time at the then [[Glenn Hoddle Academy]] club [[Jerez Industrial CF|Jerez Industrial]] in Spain. He was signed by [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in June 2013, and made his debut for the club four months later following a productive loan spell at [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]. He signed with [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in June 2014. He was loaned out to [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] in February 2015 and then [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] the following month. He was signed by Premier League side West Ham United in January 2018 for an undisclosed fee. He returned to the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] the following transfer window in a season-long loan to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] and then was loaned to Queens Park Rangers for the 2019\u201320 season.\n\n==Playing career==\n\n===Early career===\nHugill, who was a pupil at [[Nunthorpe Academy|Nunthorpe School]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=From pulling pints at the Dickens Inn to scoring at the Riverside |last=Shaw |first=Dominic |work=Gazette Live |date=27 August 2014 |accessdate=20 June 2018 |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/dickens-inn-scoring-riverside-ex-7677911}}</ref> attended [[George Smith (footballer, born 1945)|George Smith]]'s academy in [[Hemlington]] from the age of nine.<ref name=\"woody\"/> He began his career with [[Northern Football League|Northern League]] club [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]] at the age of 16, and was due to go on trial at [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] before he was struck down with an ankle injury in September 2009.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hugill injury blow for Red Star |url=http://www.sunderlandecho.com/sport/local-football-hugill-injury-blow-for-red-star-1-1070606 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=Sunderland Echo |date=18 September 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621015655/https://www.sunderlandecho.com/sport/local-football-hugill-injury-blow-for-red-star-1-1070606 |archive-date=21 June 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He later moved on to [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]], but left his contract in August 2010 to spend two years at the [[Glenn Hoddle Academy]] in Spain.<ref name=\"woody\">{{cite news |last=Woodcock |first=Laura |title=Jordan's off to train in Spain; ...with Glenn Hoddle! |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Jordan%27s+off+to+train+in+Spain%3B+...with+Glenn+Hoddle!-a0234920253 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=Evening Gazette |date=19 August 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"2 New Signings\">{{cite web |title=Marske United Make 2 New Signings |url=http://www.marskeunitedfc.com/news.htm |work=marskeunitedfc.com |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009024831/http://marskeunitedfc.com/news.htm |archivedate=9 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\nHe signed with [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]] in December 2011 and scored in his debut game against [[Nantwich Town F.C.|Nantwich Town]], only to damage his anterior cruciate ligament later in the match and spend the next ten months out injured.<ref name=\"2 New Signings\"/> He joined [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]] in October 2012 initially on loan so as to regain match fitness.<ref name=\"2 New Signings\"/> His last appearance for Marske came in the final of the [[North Riding Senior Cup]], where they were beaten 3\u20130 by [[Pickering Town F.C.|Pickering Town]].<ref name=\"mnmfg\">{{cite news |last=Steel |first=Adam |title=Cup final loss is story of Marske United's season |url=http://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/other-sport/amateur-sport/cup-final-loss-story-marske-3664998 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=gazettelive.co.uk |date=1 May 2013}}</ref> During his time at the club he worked as a barman at the ''Dickens Inn'' in [[Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill determined to be a star |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Hugill-determined-Vale-star/story-20097666-detail/story.html |accessdate=19 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=19 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121032546/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Hugill-determined-Vale-star/story-20097666-detail/story.html|archive-date=21 November 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Port Vale===\nHugill signed with [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in June 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title=Port Vale complete Chris Robertson and Gavin Tomlin deals |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23082437 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 June 2013}}</ref> He was loaned out to [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] of the [[Conference Premier]] on 20 September 2013.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Vale striker joins Gateshead |url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/Vale-striker-joins-Gateshead/story-19825034-detail/story.html#axzz2fNPmF6cX |accessdate=20 September 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=20 September 2013}}</ref> \"Tynesiders\" boss [[Gary Mills (footballer, born 1961)|Gary Mills]] stated that Hugill was a \"talented... goalscorer\" and put him in the starting line-up for the next match.<ref name=\"talent\">{{cite web |last=Bowron |first=Jeff |title=Gateshead Bring in Rams And Vale Pair |url=http://www.gateshead-fc.com/4606/gateshead-bring-in-rams-and-vale-pair |work=gateshead-fc.com |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925093727/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/4606/gateshead-bring-in-rams-and-vale-pair |archivedate=25 September 2013 }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 24 September in a 3\u20132 win over [[Chester F.C.|Chester]] at the [[Gateshead International Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gateshead 3&nbsp;\u2013 2 Chester |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24122084 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=24 September 2013}}</ref> He finished his loan spell with five goals in four starts and three substitute appearances.\n\nHe made his debut for the \"Valiants\" on 22 October, and played the first 75 minutes of a 3\u20130 victory over [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Crawley 0&nbsp;\u2013 3 Port Vale |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24529456 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=22 October 2013}}</ref> He performed well on his debut, justifying his manager's surprise decision to play him alongside fellow Glenn Hoddle Academy graduate [[Ben Williamson (footballer)|Ben Williamson]] in place of established strikers [[Tom Pope]] and [[Lee Hughes]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Michael |title=Match report: Crawley Town 0, Port Vale 3 |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Match-report-Crawley-Town-0-Port-Vale-3/story-19970607-detail/story.html |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=23 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029213432/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Match-report-Crawley-Town-0-Port-Vale-3/story-19970607-detail/story.html|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|First of all you have to say well done to our chief scout, [[George Foster (footballer)|George Foster]], who spotted his potential playing in non-league. We had him with us last season and the one thing he struggled with was his fitness. Pre-season was a struggle for him as well. He is a big old boy, not used to a professional pre-season, but is one of those lads who never gives up. You ask him to pull out of things and he doesn't want to do that.|Port Vale manager [[Micky Adams]] describing Hugill in October 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title=Micky Adams salutes Port Vale heroes after Crawley win |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Micky-Adams-salutes-Port-Vale-heroes-Crawley-win/story-19970609-detail/story.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20131024020241/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Micky-Adams-salutes-Port-Vale-heroes-Crawley-win/story-19970609-detail/story.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=24 October 2013 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=22 October 2013}}</ref>}}\n\nHe scored his first Football League goal on 16 November, scoring the final goal of a 3\u20131 victory over [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] at [[Vale Park]]; after the match Adams said that the club had \"unearthed a gem\" in Hugill.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Adams says Hugill is the real deal |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Adams-says-Hugill-real-deal/story-20090264-detail/story.html |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=16 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131118214828/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Adams-says-Hugill-real-deal/story-20090264-detail/story.html|archive-date=18 November 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hugill continued to turn out for the first team, but admitted that he needed to work on his fitness to play a full 90 minutes of professional football.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill determined to become Micky Adams' 90-minute man |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Jordan-Hugill-determined-Port-Vale-s-90-minute/story-20632004-detail/story.html |accessdate=15 February 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=15 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303175246/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Jordan-Hugill-determined-Port-Vale-s-90-minute/story-20632004-detail/story.html|archive-date=3 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> At the end of the [[2013\u201314 Port Vale F.C. season|2013\u201314]] campaign he was named as the club's Young Player of the Year, and also featured in Vale's [[Staffordshire Senior Cup]] final defeat to [[Rushall Olympic F.C.|Rushall Olympic]].<ref name=\"ddl\">{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Michael |title=Port Vale lose Staffs Senior Cup final to Rushall |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-lose-Staffs-Senior-Cup-final-Rushall/story-21036812-detail/story.html |accessdate=11 May 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=30 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512221209/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-lose-Staffs-Senior-Cup-final-Rushall/story-21036812-detail/story.html|archive-date=12 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Tom Pope named Port Vale player of the year |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Tom-Pope-named-Port-Vale-player-year/story-21056123-detail/story.html |accessdate=5 May 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=5 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505201838/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Tom-Pope-named-Port-Vale-player-year/story-21056123-detail/story.html|archive-date=5 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, in the summer Micky Adams confirmed that Hugill had rejected the club's offer of a new contract, and stated: \"It is disappointing ... we spent a lot of time and effort with Jordan last season, but we will have to accept it.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Port Vale set to lose Jordan Hugill |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-set-lose-Jordan-Hugill/story-21229649-detail/story.html |accessdate=13 June 2014 |work=t |date=13 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140616000211/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-set-lose-Jordan-Hugill/story-21229649-detail/story.html|archive-date=16 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Preston North End===\nHugill signed a two-year contract with League One club [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in June 2014, who paid Port Vale an undisclosed fee; manager [[Simon Grayson]] stated that \"he's young, he's raring to go, hungry, he's a strong, powerful player, and he's got many attributes that will help us along the way this season and complement the squad well\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End sign Port Vale striker |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27930265 |accessdate=20 June 2014 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=19 June 2014}}</ref> He had an eventful match after coming on for [[Andrew Little (footballer)|Andrew Little]] as a 20th-minute substitute at [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] on 13 September; he provided an assist for [[Joe Garner]] before being sent off for clashing with opposition defender [[Andy Butler]], he also picked up an injury in the game that required surgery and a lengthy spell on the sidelines.<ref>{{cite news |title=PNE striker undergoes knee surgery |url=http://www.lep.co.uk/sport/preston-north-end-news/pne-striker-undergoes-knee-surgery-1-6848320 |accessdate=7 October 2014 |work=Lancashire Evening Post |date=18 September 2014}}</ref> He returned to fitness in February 2015, at which point he joined his former Vale manager [[Micky Adams]] at [[EFL League Two|League Two]] side [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] for a one-month loan spell.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End striker loaned to Tranmere |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31658059 |accessdate=26 March 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 February 2015}}</ref> \n\nOn 26 March 2015, loan deadline day, Hugill signed for bottom-placed League Two club [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] on loan until the end of [[2014\u201315 Hartlepool United F.C. season|the season]]; \"Pools\" boss [[Ronnie Moore]] said that \"It just didn't work at Tranmere. But we've seen a lot of him and he'll go straight in and get goals for us, no doubt about it\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Hartlepool United: Preston striker Jordan Hugill signs on loan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32064983 |accessdate=27 March 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=26 March 2015}}</ref> He scored four goals in eight games for the club, including the winning goal against [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] at [[Victoria Park (Hartlepool)|Victoria Park]] that secured Hartlepool's place in the [[English Football League]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mennear |first1=Richard |title=Hartlepool hero Jordan Hugill eyes Preston success but hasn't ruled out a return to The Vic |url=http://www.hartlepoolmail.co.uk/sport/football/hartlepool-utd/hartlepool-hero-jordan-hugill-eyes-preston-success-but-hasn-t-ruled-out-a-return-to-the-vic-1-7234194 |accessdate=8 May 2015 |work=Hartlepool Mail |date=29 April 2015}}</ref> He was an unused substitute at [[Wembley Stadium|Wembley]] in the [[2015 Football League One play-off Final|play-off final]] as Preston won promotion into the [[EFL Championship|Championship]].<ref name=2015POF>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32770740 |title=Preston North End 4\u20130 Swindon Town |first=Nathan |last=Middleton |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2015 |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe signed a new two-and-a-half-year contract in October 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End striker signs new deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34541222 |accessdate=17 October 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=15 October 2015}}</ref> He ended the [[2015\u201316 Preston North End F.C. season|2015\u201316]] campaign with five goals in 32 games. He continued to impress in the [[2016\u201317 Preston North End F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season, and was given another new two-and-a-half-year contract in September 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill Signs New Contract |url=http://www.pnefc.net/news/article/2016-17/jordan-hugill-signs-new-contract-3308037.aspx |accessdate=12 January 2017 |work=pnefc.net |date=14 September 2016}}</ref> The club rejected an offer of \u00a31.5 million from [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] in January 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End turn down Ipswich Town approach |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38594277 |accessdate=12 January 2017 |work=BBC Sport |date=12 January 2017}}</ref> He ended the [[2016\u201317 Preston North End F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season with 13 goals in 47 appearances to end up as Preston's top-scorer.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Seddon |first1=Dave |title=PNE striker on the radar of Championship rivals |url=http://www.lep.co.uk/sport/football/preston-north-end/pne-striker-on-the-radar-of-championship-rivals-1-8536589 |accessdate=12 May 2017 |work=Lancashire Post |date=11 May 2017 |language=en}}</ref> He started the [[2017\u201318 Preston North End F.C. season|2017\u201318]] season in good form and was linked with a number of clubs in the [[List of English football transfers summer 2017|summer transfer window]]. He handed in a transfer request on 29 August 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Preston striker Jordan Hugill hands in transfer request |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11697/11011344/preston-striker-jordan-hugill-hands-in-transfer-request |accessdate=29 August 2017 |work=Sky Sports |date=29 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===West Ham United===\nOn 31 January 2018, Hugill completed a deadline day signing for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in a reported \u00a310 million transfer deal, becoming manager [[David Moyes]]' second signing at the [[London Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: West Ham sign Preston striker in reported \u00a310m deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42895867 |accessdate=1 February 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> However he was restricted to a handful of brief cameos in the second half of the [[2017\u201318 West Ham United F.C. season|2017\u201318]] season, playing just 22 minutes in total.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Inkersole |first1=Sam |title=Jordan Hugill \u2013 Why his West Ham career is yet to take off |url=https://www.football.london/west-ham-united-fc/players/jordan-hugill-west-ham-future-14484202 |accessdate=11 May 2018 |work=footballlondon |date=6 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Inkersole |first1=Sam |title=Why Jordan Hugill was not named in the West Ham squad to face Everton |url=https://www.football.london/west-ham-united-fc/players/jordan-hugill-west-ham-everton-14651777 |accessdate=14 May 2018 |work=footballlondon |date=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Middlesbrough loan====\nOn 8 August 2018, Hugill returned to the Championship on a season-long loan to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill joins Middlesbrough on loan from West Ham |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11680/11465611/jordan-hugill-closing-in-on-middlesbrough-loan-move-as-west-ham-enter-talks |accessdate=8 August 2018 |work=Sky Sports |date=8 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On 10 November, he opened his league account for the club by scoring both goals in a 2\u20130 win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] at the [[Riverside Stadium]] and was subsequently named on the EFL team of the week.<ref>{{cite news |title=Matchday 17: Team of the Week |url=https://www.efl.com/news/2018/november/matchday-17-team-of-the-week2/ |accessdate=8 October 2019 |work=www.efl.com |date=12 November 2018 |language=en-gb}}</ref> He battled with [[Britt Assombalonga]] for the role as target man striker and scored seven goals in 41 appearances during the [[2018\u201319 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2018\u201319]] season as [[Tony Pulis]]'s \"Boro\" side missed out on the play-offs by one point.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Shaw |first1=Dominic |title=Hugill, deal from 'a different stratosphere' & the need for form |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/jordan-hugill-financials-a-different-15961706 |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=gazettelive |date=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n====QPR loan====\nOn 28 July 2019, Hugill joined Championship side [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] on loan for the [[2019\u201320 Queens Park Rangers F.C. season|2019\u201320]] season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: QPR sign West Ham United striker on season-long loan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49144337 |accessdate=28 July 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=28 July 2019}}</ref> Manager [[Mark Warburton]] said he hoped Hugill would \"lead the line\" and link up well with fellow loanee striker [[Jan Mlakar]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Webb |first1=Matt |title=QPR sign Jordan Hugill on season-long loan |url=https://www.qpr.co.uk/news/club-news/qpr-sign-jordan-hugill-on-season-long-loan/ |accessdate=28 July 2019 |work=QPR |date=28 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref> He scored on his \"Hoops\" debut on 3 August as they recorded a season opening 2\u20131 victory at [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Stoke City 1-2 QPR: Jordan Hugill on target to give Mark Warburton winning start |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49135726 |accessdate=3 August 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=3 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nHugill is a target man [[Forward (association football)|forward]], has great strength and is able to out-muscle opposition defenders.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Baggaley |first1=Mike |title=Tom Pope: Why former Port Vale striker Jordan Hugill is in demand |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/tom-pope-why-former-port-vale-striker-jordan-hugill-is-in-demand/story-30054123-detail/story.html |accessdate=13 January 2017 |work=Stoke Sentinel |date=13 January 2017}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ice-cool striker Jordan Hugill gives manager Micky Adams food for thought |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Ice-cool-striker-Jordan-Hugill-gives/story-19985687-detail/story.html |accessdate=25 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=25 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029210253/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Ice-cool-striker-Jordan-Hugill-gives/story-19985687-detail/story.html|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Former Port Vale teammate [[Tom Pope]] stated that Hugill had an excellent attitude and \"was desperate to learn and improve\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pope |first1=Tom |title=Deadline day paid off for Jordan Hugill and Louis Dodds, by Port Vale's Tom Pope |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/deadline-day-paid-jordan-hugill-1154256 |accessdate=2 February 2018 |work=Stoke Sentinel |date=2 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 7 March 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Port Vale F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"13/14\">{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2013|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|20||4||4||1||0||0||0||0||24||5\n|-\n||[[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] (loan)\n|[[2013\u201314 Gateshead F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"13/14\"/>\n|[[National League (division)|Conference Premier]]\n|7||5||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||5\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]\n|[[2014\u201315 Preston North End F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"14/15\">{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2014|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|League One\n|3||0||0||0||2||1||1{{efn|Appearance in the [[EFL Trophy|League Trophy]]}}||1||6||2\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Preston North End F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2015|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|[[EFL Championship|Championship]]\n|29||3||1||0||2||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||32||5\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Preston North End F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2016|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|44||12||1||0||2||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||47||13\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Preston North End F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"2017/18\">{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2017|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|27||8||1||0||1||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||10\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!103!!23!!3!!0!!7!!6!!1!!1!!114!!30\n|-\n|[[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] (loan)\n|[[2014\u201315 Tranmere Rovers F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"14/15\"/>\n|[[EFL League Two|League Two]]\n|6||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||1\n|-\n|[[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan)\n|[[2014\u201315 Hartlepool United F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=\"14/15\"/>\n|League Two\n|8||4||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||8||4\n|-\n|[[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]\n|[[2017\u201318 West Ham United F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=\"2017/18\"/>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n|[[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] (loan)\n|[[2018\u201319 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=\"18/19\">{{Soccerbase season|72606|2018|accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|37||6||1||0||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||41||7\n|-\n|[[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] (loan)\n|[[2019\u201320 Queens Park Rangers F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=\"19/20\">{{Soccerbase season|72606|2019|accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|35||10||2||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||37||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total{{efn|name=not|Statistics for [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]], [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]], [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]] and [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]] not recorded}}\n!219!!53!!10!!3!!10!!7!!1!!1!!240!!64\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Marske United'''\n*[[North Riding Senior Cup]] runner-up: 2012\u201313<ref name=\"mnmfg\"/>\n\n'''Port Vale'''\n*[[Staffordshire Senior Cup]] runner-up: 2013\u201314<ref name=\"ddl\"/>\n\n'''Preston North End'''\n*[[Football League One play-offs]]: [[2015 Football League play-offs#League One|2015]]<ref name=2015POF/>\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] Young Player of the Year: [[2013\u201314 Port Vale F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"ddl\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Queens Park Rangers F.C. squad}}\n<!--{{West Ham United F.C. squad}}-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hugill, Jordan}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Middlesbrough]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Seaham Red Star F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Consett A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Whitby Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Marske United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Port Vale F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Gateshead F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Preston North End F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Tranmere Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:West Ham United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Middlesbrough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Queens Park Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Northern Football League players]]\n[[Category:Northern Premier League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Jordan Hugill\n| image               = Jordan Hugill.jpg\n| caption             = Hugill with Preston North End in 2016\n| fullname            = Jordan Thomas Hugill<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=18 February 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1992|06|04}}\n| birth_place         = [[Middlesbrough]], England\n| height              = {{height|ft=6|in=0}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Player Profile |url=http://mobile.pnefc.net/team/player-profile/jordan-hugill/25 |website=mobile.pnefc.net |accessdate=2 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011081207/http://mobile.pnefc.net/team/player-profile/jordan-hugill/25|archive-date=11 October 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub         = [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]]<br>(on loan from [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]])\n| clubnumber          = 9\n| youthyears1         = 2007\u20132008| youthclubs1 = [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]]\n| years1              = 2008\u20132009| clubs1 = [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]]                 | caps1 =     | goals1 = \n| years2              = 2009\u20132010| clubs2 = [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]]                               | caps2 =     | goals2 = \n| years3              = 2011     | clubs3 = [[Jerez Industrial CF|Jerez Industrial]]                 | caps3 =     | goals3 = \n| years4              = 2011\u20132012| clubs4 = [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]]                         | caps4 =     | goals4 = \n| years5              = 2012     | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]] (loan)            | caps5 =     | goals5 = \n| years6              = 2013\u20132014| clubs6 = [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]                             | caps6 =  20 | goals6 =   4\n| years7              = 2013     | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] (loan)                    | caps7 =   7 | goals7 =   5\n| years8              = 2014\u20132018| clubs8 = [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]             | caps8 = 103 | goals8 =  23\n| years9              = 2015     | clubs9 = \u2192 [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] (loan)        | caps9 =   6 | goals9 =   1\n| years10             = 2015     | clubs10= \u2192 [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (loan)    | caps10=   8 | goals10=   4\n| years11             = 2018\u2013    | clubs11= [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]]                 | caps11=   3 | goals11=   0\n| years12             = 2018\u20132019| clubs12= \u2192 [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] (loan)            | caps12=  37 | goals12=   6 \n| years13             = 2019\u2013    | clubs13= \u2192 [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] (loan)| caps13=   35| goals13=   11\n| club-update         = 18:08, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Jordan Thomas Hugill''' (born 4 June 1992) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]], on loan from [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]].\n\nA relative late comer to the professional game, he had spells with non-league sides [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]], [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]], [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]] and [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]], and also spent time at the then [[Glenn Hoddle Academy]] club [[Jerez Industrial CF|Jerez Industrial]] in Spain. He was signed by [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in June 2013, and made his debut for the club four months later following a productive loan spell at [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]. He signed with [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in June 2014. He was loaned out to [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] in February 2015 and then [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] the following month. He was signed by Premier League side West Ham United in January 2018 for an undisclosed fee. He returned to the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] the following transfer window in a season-long loan to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] and then was loaned to Queens Park Rangers for the 2019\u201320 season.\n\n==Playing career==\n\n===Early career===\nHugill, who was a pupil at [[Nunthorpe Academy|Nunthorpe School]],<ref>{{Cite web |title=From pulling pints at the Dickens Inn to scoring at the Riverside |last=Shaw |first=Dominic |work=Gazette Live |date=27 August 2014 |accessdate=20 June 2018 |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/dickens-inn-scoring-riverside-ex-7677911}}</ref> attended [[George Smith (footballer, born 1945)|George Smith]]'s academy in [[Hemlington]] from the age of nine.<ref name=\"woody\"/> He began his career with [[Northern Football League|Northern League]] club [[Seaham Red Star F.C.|Seaham Red Star]] at the age of 16, and was due to go on trial at [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] before he was struck down with an ankle injury in September 2009.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hugill injury blow for Red Star |url=http://www.sunderlandecho.com/sport/local-football-hugill-injury-blow-for-red-star-1-1070606 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=Sunderland Echo |date=18 September 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621015655/https://www.sunderlandecho.com/sport/local-football-hugill-injury-blow-for-red-star-1-1070606 |archive-date=21 June 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He later moved on to [[Consett A.F.C.|Consett]], but left his contract in August 2010 to spend two years at the [[Glenn Hoddle Academy]] in Spain.<ref name=\"woody\">{{cite news |last=Woodcock |first=Laura |title=Jordan's off to train in Spain; ...with Glenn Hoddle! |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Jordan%27s+off+to+train+in+Spain%3B+...with+Glenn+Hoddle!-a0234920253 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=Evening Gazette |date=19 August 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"2 New Signings\">{{cite web |title=Marske United Make 2 New Signings |url=http://www.marskeunitedfc.com/news.htm |work=marskeunitedfc.com |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009024831/http://marskeunitedfc.com/news.htm |archivedate=9 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\nHe signed with [[Whitby Town F.C.|Whitby Town]] in December 2011 and scored in his debut game against [[Nantwich Town F.C.|Nantwich Town]], only to damage his anterior cruciate ligament later in the match and spend the next ten months out injured.<ref name=\"2 New Signings\"/> He joined [[Marske United F.C.|Marske United]] in October 2012 initially on loan so as to regain match fitness.<ref name=\"2 New Signings\"/> His last appearance for Marske came in the final of the [[North Riding Senior Cup]], where they were beaten 3\u20130 by [[Pickering Town F.C.|Pickering Town]].<ref name=\"mnmfg\">{{cite news |last=Steel |first=Adam |title=Cup final loss is story of Marske United's season |url=http://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/other-sport/amateur-sport/cup-final-loss-story-marske-3664998 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=gazettelive.co.uk |date=1 May 2013}}</ref> During his time at the club he worked as a barman at the ''Dickens Inn'' in [[Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill determined to be a star |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Hugill-determined-Vale-star/story-20097666-detail/story.html |accessdate=19 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=19 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131121032546/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Hugill-determined-Vale-star/story-20097666-detail/story.html|archive-date=21 November 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Port Vale===\nHugill signed with [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in June 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title=Port Vale complete Chris Robertson and Gavin Tomlin deals |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23082437 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 June 2013}}</ref> He was loaned out to [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] of the [[Conference Premier]] on 20 September 2013.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Vale striker joins Gateshead |url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/Vale-striker-joins-Gateshead/story-19825034-detail/story.html#axzz2fNPmF6cX |accessdate=20 September 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=20 September 2013}}</ref> \"Tynesiders\" boss [[Gary Mills (footballer, born 1961)|Gary Mills]] stated that Hugill was a \"talented... goalscorer\" and put him in the starting line-up for the next match.<ref name=\"talent\">{{cite web |last=Bowron |first=Jeff |title=Gateshead Bring in Rams And Vale Pair |url=http://www.gateshead-fc.com/4606/gateshead-bring-in-rams-and-vale-pair |work=gateshead-fc.com |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130925093727/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/4606/gateshead-bring-in-rams-and-vale-pair |archivedate=25 September 2013 }}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 24 September in a 3\u20132 win over [[Chester F.C.|Chester]] at the [[Gateshead International Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gateshead 3&nbsp;\u2013 2 Chester |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24122084 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=24 September 2013}}</ref> He finished his loan spell with five goals in four starts and three substitute appearances.\n\nHe made his debut for the \"Valiants\" on 22 October, and played the first 75 minutes of a 3\u20130 victory over [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Crawley 0&nbsp;\u2013 3 Port Vale |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/24529456 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=22 October 2013}}</ref> He performed well on his debut, justifying his manager's surprise decision to play him alongside fellow Glenn Hoddle Academy graduate [[Ben Williamson (footballer)|Ben Williamson]] in place of established strikers [[Tom Pope]] and [[Lee Hughes]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Michael |title=Match report: Crawley Town 0, Port Vale 3 |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Match-report-Crawley-Town-0-Port-Vale-3/story-19970607-detail/story.html |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=23 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029213432/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Match-report-Crawley-Town-0-Port-Vale-3/story-19970607-detail/story.html|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|First of all you have to say well done to our chief scout, [[George Foster (footballer)|George Foster]], who spotted his potential playing in non-league. We had him with us last season and the one thing he struggled with was his fitness. Pre-season was a struggle for him as well. He is a big old boy, not used to a professional pre-season, but is one of those lads who never gives up. You ask him to pull out of things and he doesn't want to do that.|Port Vale manager [[Micky Adams]] describing Hugill in October 2013.<ref>{{cite news |title=Micky Adams salutes Port Vale heroes after Crawley win |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Micky-Adams-salutes-Port-Vale-heroes-Crawley-win/story-19970609-detail/story.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20131024020241/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Micky-Adams-salutes-Port-Vale-heroes-Crawley-win/story-19970609-detail/story.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=24 October 2013 |accessdate=23 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=22 October 2013}}</ref>}}\n\nHe scored his first Football League goal on 16 November, scoring the final goal of a 3\u20131 victory over [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] at [[Vale Park]]; after the match Adams said that the club had \"unearthed a gem\" in Hugill.<ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Adams says Hugill is the real deal |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Adams-says-Hugill-real-deal/story-20090264-detail/story.html |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=16 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131118214828/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Adams-says-Hugill-real-deal/story-20090264-detail/story.html|archive-date=18 November 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Hugill continued to turn out for the first team, but admitted that he needed to work on his fitness to play a full 90 minutes of professional football.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill determined to become Micky Adams' 90-minute man |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Jordan-Hugill-determined-Port-Vale-s-90-minute/story-20632004-detail/story.html |accessdate=15 February 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=15 February 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140303175246/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Jordan-Hugill-determined-Port-Vale-s-90-minute/story-20632004-detail/story.html|archive-date=3 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> At the end of the [[2013\u201314 Port Vale F.C. season|2013\u201314]] campaign he was named as the club's Young Player of the Year, and also featured in Vale's [[Staffordshire Senior Cup]] final defeat to [[Rushall Olympic F.C.|Rushall Olympic]].<ref name=\"ddl\">{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Michael |title=Port Vale lose Staffs Senior Cup final to Rushall |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-lose-Staffs-Senior-Cup-final-Rushall/story-21036812-detail/story.html |accessdate=11 May 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=30 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512221209/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-lose-Staffs-Senior-Cup-final-Rushall/story-21036812-detail/story.html|archive-date=12 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Baggaley |first=Mike |title=Tom Pope named Port Vale player of the year |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Tom-Pope-named-Port-Vale-player-year/story-21056123-detail/story.html |accessdate=5 May 2014 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=5 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505201838/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Tom-Pope-named-Port-Vale-player-year/story-21056123-detail/story.html|archive-date=5 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> However, in the summer Micky Adams confirmed that Hugill had rejected the club's offer of a new contract, and stated: \"It is disappointing ... we spent a lot of time and effort with Jordan last season, but we will have to accept it.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Port Vale set to lose Jordan Hugill |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-set-lose-Jordan-Hugill/story-21229649-detail/story.html |accessdate=13 June 2014 |work=t |date=13 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140616000211/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-set-lose-Jordan-Hugill/story-21229649-detail/story.html|archive-date=16 June 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Preston North End===\nHugill signed a two-year contract with League One club [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]] in June 2014, who paid Port Vale an undisclosed fee; manager [[Simon Grayson]] stated that \"he's young, he's raring to go, hungry, he's a strong, powerful player, and he's got many attributes that will help us along the way this season and complement the squad well\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End sign Port Vale striker |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27930265 |accessdate=20 June 2014 |newspaper=[[BBC Sport]] |date=19 June 2014}}</ref> He had an eventful match after coming on for [[Andrew Little (footballer)|Andrew Little]] as a 20th-minute substitute at [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] on 13 September; he provided an assist for [[Joe Garner]] before being sent off for clashing with opposition defender [[Andy Butler]], he also picked up an injury in the game that required surgery and a lengthy spell on the sidelines.<ref>{{cite news |title=PNE striker undergoes knee surgery |url=http://www.lep.co.uk/sport/preston-north-end-news/pne-striker-undergoes-knee-surgery-1-6848320 |accessdate=7 October 2014 |work=Lancashire Evening Post |date=18 September 2014}}</ref> He returned to fitness in February 2015, at which point he joined his former Vale manager [[Micky Adams]] at [[EFL League Two|League Two]] side [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]] for a one-month loan spell.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End striker loaned to Tranmere |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31658059 |accessdate=26 March 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 February 2015}}</ref> \n\nOn 26 March 2015, loan deadline day, Hugill signed for bottom-placed League Two club [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] on loan until the end of [[2014\u201315 Hartlepool United F.C. season|the season]]; \"Pools\" boss [[Ronnie Moore]] said that \"It just didn't work at Tranmere. But we've seen a lot of him and he'll go straight in and get goals for us, no doubt about it\".<ref>{{cite news |title=Hartlepool United: Preston striker Jordan Hugill signs on loan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32064983 |accessdate=27 March 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=26 March 2015}}</ref> He scored four goals in eight games for the club, including the winning goal against [[Exeter City F.C.|Exeter City]] at [[Victoria Park (Hartlepool)|Victoria Park]] that secured Hartlepool's place in the [[English Football League]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mennear |first1=Richard |title=Hartlepool hero Jordan Hugill eyes Preston success but hasn't ruled out a return to The Vic |url=http://www.hartlepoolmail.co.uk/sport/football/hartlepool-utd/hartlepool-hero-jordan-hugill-eyes-preston-success-but-hasn-t-ruled-out-a-return-to-the-vic-1-7234194 |accessdate=8 May 2015 |work=Hartlepool Mail |date=29 April 2015}}</ref> He was an unused substitute at [[Wembley Stadium|Wembley]] in the [[2015 Football League One play-off Final|play-off final]] as Preston won promotion into the [[EFL Championship|Championship]].<ref name=2015POF>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/32770740 |title=Preston North End 4\u20130 Swindon Town |first=Nathan |last=Middleton |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 May 2015 |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe signed a new two-and-a-half-year contract in October 2015.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End striker signs new deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34541222 |accessdate=17 October 2015 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=15 October 2015}}</ref> He ended the [[2015\u201316 Preston North End F.C. season|2015\u201316]] campaign with five goals in 32 games. He continued to impress in the [[2016\u201317 Preston North End F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season, and was given another new two-and-a-half-year contract in September 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill Signs New Contract |url=http://www.pnefc.net/news/article/2016-17/jordan-hugill-signs-new-contract-3308037.aspx |accessdate=12 January 2017 |work=pnefc.net |date=14 September 2016}}</ref> The club rejected an offer of \u00a31.5 million from [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] in January 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: Preston North End turn down Ipswich Town approach |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38594277 |accessdate=12 January 2017 |work=BBC Sport |date=12 January 2017}}</ref> He ended the [[2016\u201317 Preston North End F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season with 13 goals in 47 appearances to end up as Preston's top-scorer.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Seddon |first1=Dave |title=PNE striker on the radar of Championship rivals |url=http://www.lep.co.uk/sport/football/preston-north-end/pne-striker-on-the-radar-of-championship-rivals-1-8536589 |accessdate=12 May 2017 |work=Lancashire Post |date=11 May 2017 |language=en}}</ref> He started the [[2017\u201318 Preston North End F.C. season|2017\u201318]] season in good form and was linked with a number of clubs in the [[List of English football transfers summer 2017|summer transfer window]]. He handed in a transfer request on 29 August 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=Preston striker Jordan Hugill hands in transfer request |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11697/11011344/preston-striker-jordan-hugill-hands-in-transfer-request |accessdate=29 August 2017 |work=Sky Sports |date=29 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===West Ham United===\nOn 31 January 2018, Hugill completed a deadline day signing for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] in a reported \u00a310 million transfer deal, becoming manager [[David Moyes]]' second signing at the [[London Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: West Ham sign Preston striker in reported \u00a310m deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42895867 |accessdate=1 February 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=31 January 2018}}</ref> However he was restricted to a handful of brief cameos in the second half of the [[2017\u201318 West Ham United F.C. season|2017\u201318]] season, playing just 22 minutes in total.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Inkersole |first1=Sam |title=Jordan Hugill \u2013 Why his West Ham career is yet to take off |url=https://www.football.london/west-ham-united-fc/players/jordan-hugill-west-ham-future-14484202 |accessdate=11 May 2018 |work=footballlondon |date=6 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Inkersole |first1=Sam |title=Why Jordan Hugill was not named in the West Ham squad to face Everton |url=https://www.football.london/west-ham-united-fc/players/jordan-hugill-west-ham-everton-14651777 |accessdate=14 May 2018 |work=footballlondon |date=13 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Middlesbrough loan====\nOn 8 August 2018, Hugill returned to the Championship on a season-long loan to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill joins Middlesbrough on loan from West Ham |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11680/11465611/jordan-hugill-closing-in-on-middlesbrough-loan-move-as-west-ham-enter-talks |accessdate=8 August 2018 |work=Sky Sports |date=8 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref> On 10 November, he opened his league account for the club by scoring both goals in a 2\u20130 win over [[Wigan Athletic F.C.|Wigan Athletic]] at the [[Riverside Stadium]] and was subsequently named on the EFL team of the week.<ref>{{cite news |title=Matchday 17: Team of the Week |url=https://www.efl.com/news/2018/november/matchday-17-team-of-the-week2/ |accessdate=8 October 2019 |work=www.efl.com |date=12 November 2018 |language=en-gb}}</ref> He battled with [[Britt Assombalonga]] for the role as target man striker and scored seven goals in 41 appearances during the [[2018\u201319 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2018\u201319]] season as [[Tony Pulis]]'s \"Boro\" side missed out on the play-offs by one point.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Shaw |first1=Dominic |title=Hugill, deal from 'a different stratosphere' & the need for form |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/jordan-hugill-financials-a-different-15961706 |accessdate=6 May 2019 |work=gazettelive |date=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n====QPR loan====\nOn 28 July 2019, Hugill joined Championship side [[Queens Park Rangers F.C.|Queens Park Rangers]] on loan for the [[2019\u201320 Queens Park Rangers F.C. season|2019\u201320]] season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jordan Hugill: QPR sign West Ham United striker on season-long loan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49144337 |accessdate=28 July 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=28 July 2019}}</ref> Manager [[Mark Warburton]] said he hoped Hugill would \"lead the line\" and link up well with fellow loanee striker [[Jan Mlakar]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Webb |first1=Matt |title=QPR sign Jordan Hugill on season-long loan |url=https://www.qpr.co.uk/news/club-news/qpr-sign-jordan-hugill-on-season-long-loan/ |accessdate=28 July 2019 |work=QPR |date=28 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref> He scored on his \"Hoops\" debut on 3 August as they recorded a season opening 2\u20131 victory at [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Stoke City 1-2 QPR: Jordan Hugill on target to give Mark Warburton winning start |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49135726 |accessdate=3 August 2019 |work=BBC Sport |date=3 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nHugill is a target man [[Forward (association football)|forward]], has great strength and is able to out-muscle opposition defenders.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Baggaley |first1=Mike |title=Tom Pope: Why former Port Vale striker Jordan Hugill is in demand |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/tom-pope-why-former-port-vale-striker-jordan-hugill-is-in-demand/story-30054123-detail/story.html |accessdate=13 January 2017 |work=Stoke Sentinel |date=13 January 2017}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Ice-cool striker Jordan Hugill gives manager Micky Adams food for thought |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Ice-cool-striker-Jordan-Hugill-gives/story-19985687-detail/story.html |accessdate=25 October 2013 |newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]] |date=25 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029210253/http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/Port-Vale-Ice-cool-striker-Jordan-Hugill-gives/story-19985687-detail/story.html|archive-date=29 October 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Former Port Vale teammate [[Tom Pope]] stated that Hugill had an excellent attitude and \"was desperate to learn and improve\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pope |first1=Tom |title=Deadline day paid off for Jordan Hugill and Louis Dodds, by Port Vale's Tom Pope |url=http://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/deadline-day-paid-jordan-hugill-1154256 |accessdate=2 February 2018 |work=Stoke Sentinel |date=2 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 15 February 2020}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]\n|[[2013\u201314 Port Vale F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=\"13/14\">{{Soccerbase season|id=72606|season=2013|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|20||4|