ahit Isang Saglit <small>(Minus One)</small>\n| length10        = 4:46\n| extra10         = Juris\n| title11         = Gaano Kadalas Ang Minsan <small>(Minus One)</small>\n| length11        = 4:07\n| extra11         = Christian Bautista\n| title12         = Hanggang Sa Dulo Ng Walang Hanggan <small>(Minus One)</small>\n| length12        = 3:18\n| extra12         = Nina\n}}\n\n[[Insert song]]s also include \"''Natutulog Ba Ang Diyos?''\" by Gary Valenciano (from the 2008 album Rebirth) and \"''Kastilyong Buhangin''\" by [[Regine Velasquez]] (from the 1991 album [[Tagala Talaga]]). For the final ten episodes, unreleased songs include the [[orchestra]]l versions of \"''Dadalhin''\" by Bryan Termulo and \"''Hanggang Sa Dulo Ng Walang Hanggan''\" by Gary Valenciano, both arranged by the [[ABS-CBN Philharmonic Orchestra]] and the Ateneo Chamber Singers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/10/26/12/walang-hanggans-10-most-memorable-scenes|title=Walang Hanggan's 10 most memorable scenes|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=26 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\n===Marketing===\nThe first full-length trailer was released on 17 December 2011 via the drama-anthology ''[[Maalaala Mo Kaya]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2011/12/16/758598/walang-hanggan-full-trailer-preems-dec-17|title=Walang Hanggan full trailer preems Dec. 17|newspaper=[[The Philippine Star]]|first=Rosalinda L.|last=Orosa|date=16 December 2011|accessdate=29 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nFrom 9 to 13 January 2012, the cast members of the series appeared via the morning talk show ''[[Kris TV]]'' where they promoted the series. First to make an appearance were Richard Gomez and Dawn Zulueta,<ref>[https://twitter.com/KrisTV_Official/status/156176108117688320 Richard Gomez and Dawn Zulueta appears on Kris TV]</ref> followed by the artists of the ''Walang Hanggan: The Official Soundtrack'' album.<ref>[https://twitter.com/KrisTV_Official/status/156538459555770369 The singers of Walang Hanggan: The Official Soundtrack album guests on Kris TV]</ref> On 11 January, Julia Montes, Melissa Ricks, Joem Bascon and Paulo Avelino promoted their latest drama.<ref>[https://twitter.com/KrisTV_Official/status/156894496569827329 Julia Montes, Melissa Ricks, Paulo Avelino and Joem Bascon promotes their latest drama 'Walang Hanggan']</ref> This was followed by a guest appearance of Helen Gamboa and Susan Roces on 12 January.<ref>[https://twitter.com/KrisTV_Official/status/157110814850023425 Helen Gamboa-Sotto and Susan Roces visits Kris TV]</ref> By 13 January, Coco Martin, the series' lead actor who coincidentally is the talk show's most requested guest,<ref>[http://kris.abs-cbn.com/lifecast/id/7d17d2f0-d66d-441e-a76f-b723368f1272 Coco Martin is \"most requested\" guest on Kris TV]</ref> gave a special appearance.<ref>[https://twitter.com/KrisTV_Official/status/157630972194586624 Coco Martin promotes Walang Hanggan on Kris TV]</ref>\n\nGomez once again promoted the series by guesting in the noontime variety show ''[[Happy, Yipee, Yehey]]'' on 14 January,<ref>[http://www.abs-cbn.com/Feature/Article/10696/Richard-Gomez-joins-Happy-Yipee-Yehey-this-Saturday.aspx Richard Gomez joins Happy Yipee Yehey this Saturday]</ref> the same day of the series' advanced special screening held at [[SM Megamall]],<ref>[https://twitter.com/ericjohnsalut/status/157730577603235840 Eric John Salut confirms Walang Hanggan's special screening via Twitter]</ref> the screening was attended by many acclaimed artists and critics namely Gomez' wife [[Lucy Torres]] with [[Kris Aquino]], [[Vice Ganda]] and Liz Uy.<ref>[https://twitter.com/vicegandako/status/158139576244908032 Vice Ganda watches Walang Hanggan's special screening with Lucy Torres, Kris Aquino and Liz Uy]</ref> Also present in the said screening was ''[[My Binondo Girl]]'s'' Richard Yap, Zulueta's husband Cong. Anton Lagdameo, and Garrie Concepcion.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QFDmEO-vvbY&list=UUCPwc1WaDxWccvl1n5j-oUA&index=1&feature=plcp My Binondo Girl's Richard Yap attends Walang Hanggan's special screening]</ref>\n\nOn 15 January, the cast visited at [[SM City North EDSA|SM North Skydome]] for a Grand Fans Day and for the release of the series' original soundtrack,<ref name=\"soundtrack\">[http://www.twitlonger.com/show/fa420q  Walang Hanggan's soundtrack will hit the markets on January 15]</ref> they also guested in the musical variety show ''[[ASAP (variety show)|ASAP]]'',<ref>[https://twitter.com/ASAPOFFICIAL/status/158169055356919808 Walang Hanggan cast guests on ASAP 2012]</ref> followed by another appearance of Gomez in the late-night talk show ''[[Gandang Gabi, Vice!]]''<ref>[https://twitter.com/GGViceyungtotoo/status/158507775704571905 Richard Gomez guests in Gandang Gabi, Vice!]</ref> while Paulo Avelino guested in ''[[The Buzz (talk show)|The Buzz]]''.<ref>[https://twitter.com/mepauloavelino/status/158395737883938816 Paulo Avelino guests in The Buzz]</ref>\n\nAfter its successful premiere and the viewer's warm support, the cast launched ''Pagmamahalang Walang Hanggan: The Nationwide Mall Tour''. In 5 February, the cast visited [[SM City Lucena]] followed by an appearance in 12 February at [[SM City Pampanga]].<ref>[http://manilarepublic.com/walang-hanggan-phs-no-1-tv-program-in-january/1572 Walang Hanggan cast visits SM Lucena next SM Pampanga]</ref> In 18 February, the cast continued their appreciation stopping at Gaisano Capital Mall in Mactan, Cebu City.<ref>[http://www.facebook.com/abs.walanghanggan/posts/384480088235625 Paulo, Coco and Julia in Gaisano Capital Mall Mactan]</ref> In 25 February, Coco Martin visited Koronadal, General Santos City as well as being part of the ''Fun Feb Night''<ref>[http://southcotabato.gov.ph/main/?p=3795 Coco Martin in Fun Feb Night]</ref> concert with [[Jed Madela]] and Juris to promote the drama.<ref name=\"tourfebmarch\">{{cite news|last=Galindez|first=Flow|title=Catch Coco Martin and Julia Montes on Walang Hanggan Mall Tour|url=http://angsawariko.com/2012/02/catch-coco-martin-and-julia-montes-on-walang-hanggan-mall-tour/|accessdate=31 October 2012|newspaper=ASK l|date=9 February 2012}}</ref>  In 3 March, Martin, Ricks, Avelino, Bascon and Montes stopped by at Panagbenga Festival in [[Baguio City]].<ref name=\"tourfebmarch\" /> The cast continued the tour in Gaisano Mall of Davao Atrium in 17 March<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ArWG1VoPNsQ&context=C4464068VDvjVQa1PpcFMJoZ-GBr3iCh2KaTa-nmt_zqZvrEtWy0Y= March 17 mall tour, Walang Hanggan]</ref> and was followed by a tour at Panaad Stadium Bacolod City in 14 April.<ref>[https://twitter.com/WalangHanggan_/status/186806546326499328 April 14 mall tour: Panaad Festival]</ref>\n\n===Merchandising===\nABS-CBN took advantage of the drama's popularity to partner with local jeweler Karat World to produce an \"infinity ring,\" a special ring shaped like intertwined [[Infinite loop|infinity loops]]. The rings are available in 14-karat solid yellow gold, 14-karat solid white gold, and silver 925. Each ring also has an \"infinity marking\" and a 585-stamping \"to signify its gold purity.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/lifestyle/03/30/12/%E2%80%98infinity-rings%E2%80%99-targeted-die-hard-%E2%80%98walang-hanggan%E2%80%99-fans|title=\u2018Infinity rings\u2019 targeted at die-hard \u2018Walang Hanggan\u2019 fans|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=30 March 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> They also released infinity necklaces and earrings.\n\n==Reception==\n===Ratings===\nThe series finale episode on 26 October 2012 drew in a record-breaking 45.4% nationwide audience share, topping its previous all-time highest rating of 44.7%. The drama also captivated the viewers and netizens on social networking sites, becoming the most talked-about topic online. The drama's title was the number one worldwide trending topic on Twitter during the airing of final episode.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/10/30/12/walang-hanggan-finale-scores-all-time-high-rating|title='Walang Hanggan' finale scores all-time high rating|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=30 October 2012|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> According to a release from [[Kantar Media|Kantar Media-TNS]] data, ''Walang Hanggan'' is the only Filipino drama of 2012 to have surpassed the 40% margin, registering a 41% ratings share on 23 May, followed by 41.4% on 15 June, and 44.7% on 29 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/376416/walang-hanggan-wedding-scenes-shot-in-intramuros-cost-p32-m#.UQu8JB006So|title='Walang Hanggan' Wedding Scenes Shot In Intramuros, Cost P3.2 M|newspaper=[[Manila Bulletin]]|first=Jojo P.|last=Panaligan|date=10 October 2012|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><!--This link is dead, contemplating on replacing it altogether unless an archived version of the link is found-->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#f9f9f9; line-height:16px;\" width=\"100%\"\n|+ KANTAR MEDIA NATIONAL TV RATINGS\n|-\n! Pilot episode !! Finale episode !! Peak !! Average !! Source\n|-\n|| '''32.1%''' <br> {{small|(16 January 2012, 9:15pm)}}\n|| '''45.4%''' <br> {{small|(26 October 2012, 8:15pm)}}\n|| '''45.4%''' <br> {{small|(26 October 2012, 8:15pm)}} <br> '''44.7%''' <br> {{small|(29 June 2012, 8:30pm)}}\n|| '''38.4%'''\n|| <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/01/18/12/walang-hanggan-pilot-leads-nationwide-tv-ratings|title='Walang Hanggan' pilot leads nationwide TV ratings|date=18 January 2014|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://philnews.ph/2012/10/30/walang-hanggan-finale-dominated-nationwide-tv-ratings/|title=Walang Hanggan Finale Dominated Nationwide TV Ratings|date=30 October 2012|first=Ed|last=Umbao|work=Philippine News|accessdate=30 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pep.ph/guide/tv/11307/abs-cbn39s-walang-hanggan-emerged-as-most-watched-show-during-